#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md
msgid "Records"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md:101
msgid ""
"An OCDS record provides a snapshot of the contracting process at a given "
"point in time, bringing together all the information from the releases to"
" date into one place. It is updated as new information becomes available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md:103
msgid ""
"At a minimum, a record should exist for each contracting process to "
"provide a list of all the releases that relate to that contracting "
"process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md:105
msgid ""
"However, to allow users to get a snapshot view the contracting process "
"without individually looking up each release , a record should also "
"contain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md:107
msgid ""
"a compiledRelease block, which follows the release schema, and is updated"
" with the most up-to-date value for each field; and, optionally,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md:108
msgid ""
"a versionedRelease, which contains a history of all the changes for each "
"field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/releases_and_records.md:110
msgid ""
"The OCDS merge strategies set out how to combine multiple releases to "
"create a single record for each contracting process."
msgstr ""

